The paper deals with multi-hop question answering, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses adversarial evaluation and training, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of baseline models and the development of new models suggest a focus on machine learning and statistical modeling (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of a control unit, which is a common technique in neural networks and deep learning (cs.NE). Finally, the paper discusses the use of contextual information and attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in computer vision and image processing (cs.CV).
